The Linux Command Line - Chapter 12 -> A Gentle Introduction to Vi(m)
---------------------------------------------------------------------
---------------------------------------------------------------------

:h -> get help-name

help-name -> /usr/share/vim/vim81/doc

#########################################################################
#########################################################################

----------------------------------
----------------------------------
>>> Editing Multiple Files: (vim start)
------------------------------ 
>> "vim file1 file2 file3"
---------------------------------
----------------------------------
>>> Add New File To Session: (in-session)
------------------------------ 
>> ":e adding-file.txt"
>> ":vertical new" (blank) 
----------------------------------
----------------------------------
>>> View All Files in Buffer
----------------------------------
>> ":args"
----------------------------------
----------------------------------
>>> Insert File Below Cursor Pos:
----------------------------------
>> ":r filename"
----------------------------------
----------------------------------
>>> Save Any File in Buffer:
----------------------------------
>> ":w filename" 
----------------------------------
----------------------------------
>>> Create a backup before edits 
----------------------------------
>> ":set backup" 
----------------------------------
----------------------------------
>>> Save Original File
----------------------------------
>> ":set patchmode=.orig" 
----------------------------------
----------------------------------
>>> Viewing Differences  
----------------------------------
>> ":vimdiff file.c~ file.c" 
----------------------------------
----------------------------------
>>> Unload/Delete Buffer
----------------------------------
>> ":bd[elete] [N]" 
----------------------------------
----------------------------------

#########################################################################
#########################################################################
 GEN/ADMIN  | ACTION
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     q      | Quit vim -> q! = to force quit
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     wq     | Save current working file & exit vim
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     ZZ     | Save current working file & exit vim
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
    :bn     | Go to 'buffer-next'
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
    :bp     | Go to 'buffer-previous'
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
  :buffers  | List all files in vim buffer
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
  :buffer#  | Go to a specific buffer index
------------|------------------------------------------------------------

#########################################################################
#########################################################################

 NAVIGATION | NAVIGIT
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     l      | Right one character
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     h      | Left one character 
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     j      | Down one line
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     k      | Up one line
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     0      | To the beginnign of the current line
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     ^      | To the first non-whitespace character on the current line
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     $      | To the end of the current line
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     w      | To beginning of the next word or punctuation character
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     W      | To beginning of the next word, ignoring punctuation
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     B      | To beginning of the previous word, ignoring punctuation
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
  numberG   | GoTo line number. "106G" -> 106th line in file
------------|------------------------------------------------------------

#########################################################################
#########################################################################

   COMMAND   | SILLY WINDOWS
-------------|------------------------------------------------------------
   :split    | Split current file (top/bottom)
-------------|------------------------------------------------------------
   :vsplit   | Split current file (left/right)
-------------|------------------------------------------------------------
  Ctrl-W; w  | Jump to next vim-window
-------------|------------------------------------------------------------
 Ctrl-W: Nav |(h,j,k,l) lowercase navigation keys to jump windows
-------------|------------------------------------------------------------
 Ctrl-W: Nav |(H,J,K,L) UPPERCASE navigation keys to MOVE windows
-------------|------------------------------------------------------------
 #Ctrl-W +/- | Resize Height: | <numLines> | <Ctrl-W> | <+/- numLines> |
-------------|------------------------------------------------------------
 #Ctrl-W >/< | Resize Width: | <numCols> | <Ctrl-W> | >right>//<left<  |
-------------|------------------------------------------------------------
   :close    | Close the current window safely
-------------|------------------------------------------------------------
   :only     | Close all windows except where active cursor resides
-------------|------------------------------------------------------------
 
#########################################################################
#########################################################################

 COMMAND(o) | OPENS
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     o      | Line below the current line
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     O      | Line above the current line
------------|------------------------------------------------------------

#########################################################################
#########################################################################

COMMAND(x|d)| DELETES
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
    x       | The current character
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
    3x      | The current character and the next two charaters
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
    dd      | The current line
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
    5dd     | The current line and the next 4 lines
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
    dw	    | From cur-cursor-pos. to end of next word
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
    d$      | The current line to EOL
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
    d^      | From cur-cursor-pos. to first non-whitespace char-in-line
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
    dG      | From current line to the end of the file
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
   d20G     | From the current line to the 20th line in file
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
  
#########################################################################
#########################################################################
  
 COMMAND(y) | COPIES -> "p" to 'paste yank'
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
    yy      | The current line
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
    5yy     | The current line and the next 5 lines
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
    y$      | Current-cursor-pos. to beginning of next word
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
    y0      | Current-cursor-pos. to beginning of the line 
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
    y^      | Cur-cursor-pos. to first non-whitespace char-in-line
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
    yG      | From the current line to the end of the file 
------------|------------------------------------------------------------

#########################################################################
######################################################################### 
 
 COMMAND(p) | OPENS
------------|------------------------------------------------------------ 
     p      | Paste yanked text at cursor location 
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     P      | Paste yanked text on line above cursor
------------|------------------------------------------------------------

#########################################################################
#########################################################################

  COMMAND   | ACTION
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     J      | Joins line below cursor to current line EOL
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     f      | Perform a line search for matching PATTERN          
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     ^-> ;  | Use semicolon to continue search over length of line
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     /      | Search complete file for instance of PATTERN
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     ^-> n  | Repeat search using previous search string
------------|------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------------------
-- GLOBAL SEARCH-AND-REPLACE --
-------------------------------
| >>>   :%s/Line/line/g  <<<  | 
-------------------------------
-------------------------------
   SEARCH   | ACTION
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     :      | The colon character starts an ex command
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
            | This specifies the range of lines for the operation
     %      | % is a shortcut for "from-first-to-last-line"
	    | The 'range' can also be specified; [ <1, 5> | <1, $> ]
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     s      | Specifies operation. Here 'substitution' (search/replace)
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
 /Line/line | Specifies search PATTERN followed by replacement text 
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
            | Indicates 'global' in the sense that search/replace is
            | performed on every instance of the search string in the
    g(c)    | line. If omitted; only first instance of the search
	    | string on each line is replaced
            | * Appending('c') asks confirmation before replace
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
############|###########
------------|----------     
  REPLACE   | ACTION
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     y      | Perform the substitution
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     n      | Skip this instance of the pattern
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     a      | Perform the sub. on this & all subsequent pattern matches
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
  q or Esc  | Quit substituting 
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
     l      | Perform the substitution, then quit. Short for 'last'
------------|------------------------------------------------------------
 Ctrl-[e|y] | Scroll down and up, respectively
------------|------------------------------------------------------------

